  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Safety of World Health Organization (WHO) Personnel in Ebola Response with Security Communications and Analysis Network (SCAAN)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Security Communications and Analysis Network (SCAAN) is a personnel security tool that uses modern communication and technology to provide personnel with real-time information on emerging threats, facilitate headcounts, and empower personnel to be in instant contact with securitypersonnel in an emergency. Developed by and for IOM personnel, the network has attracted interest and attention of UN and international organizations for its potential to save lives, particularly the World Health Organization (WHO) as they scale up to respond to the Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).This project will allow for an inception phase of SCAAN by WHO personnel working in the Ebola response to enhance their security and WHO&apos;s duty of care.</narrative>
  </description>
